Lectures in NTU














 
 










 


 








Lectures in NTU





 



Thank you very much for visiting my webpage. 
I offer very unique lecture courses (理論生態，理論演化，生態模式，C語言) in NTU for learning basic but fundamental features in ecological theory and ecological modeling. 
Any students in the fields of ecology (marine biology, terrestrial ecology, forest ecology, and microbial ecology) and also in the fields of life science, who are interested in modeling and theory, are very welcome to my courses. 
You might be also interested in the international PhD program, organized by Academia Sinica. Please check TIGP for PhD program: HERE.
Which courses fit you? --Depending on the difference in your interest, you can follow one of the following options. 
(Click HERE to download pdf version)





















Don’t worry about math and programing! --Although you may be afraid that you need to take courses in mathematical department and/or computer science before learning theoretical biology, don’t worry. I provide all materials you need to learn (basic skills in math and modeling, and more importantly the ways of thinking behind the skills) during my courses.

The following is the detailed information for each course. If you have more questions, you can make contact to me (email:tksmiki ‘at’ ntu.edu.tw) or visit my office (401 in IONTU). 
(Click HERE to download pdf version)























English Syllabus is also available at CEIBA.
The lecture webpages for 103-2.

理論演化生態學導論  (Basics in Theoretical Evolutionary Ecology) https://ceiba.ntu.edu.tw/1032Ocean5083_evol
生命科學模式 : 理論與實作 (Modeling for Life science & Ecology) https://ceiba.ntu.edu.tw/1032Ocean5090_lifemd
生態模擬：以C語言為例 (C language for Ecology) https://ceiba.ntu.edu.tw/1032Ocean5068_clang









 


 










